5. Imp classes

5.1 Indexer Imp

Purpose: Assign structure to new material

Inputs
	•	raw conversation
	•	note
	•	file
	•	extracted artifact
	•	repo update

Outputs
	•	tags
	•	category
	•	relation edges
	•	suggested placement

Typical actions
	•	attach domain labels
	•	detect entity/role associations
	•	suggest parent-child relationships
	•	mark provisional vs canonical

Example output

{
  "artifact_name": "Horse Archer Protocol",
  "tags": ["timing", "strategy", "mobility", "anticipation"],
  "related_roles": ["Spider", "Raven"],
  "status": "provisional",
  "suggested_location": "Library/Protocols/Strategy"
}


⸻

5.2 Distiller Imp

Purpose: Compress large material into reusable form

Inputs
	•	long conversation
	•	rambling note
	•	whitepaper draft
	•	brainstorm output

Outputs
	•	core idea
	•	invariant
	•	concise summary
	•	candidate protocol/spec language

Compression targets
	•	operator
	•	invariant
	•	loop
	•	role
	•	failure mode
	•	domain link

Example output schema

{
