6. Artifact states

Every Library item should exist in one of these states:

Seed

raw idea, fragment, metaphor, emerging pattern

Provisional

structured enough to preserve, not yet canonical

Canonical

reviewed and accepted into durable Pantheon doctrine

Archived

kept for provenance but no longer active

Superseded

replaced by newer, cleaner version while retaining lineage

⸻

7. Review protocol

Mother Duck Review Decision Tree

Accept as canon if:
	•	repeatable
	•	coherent with existing invariants
	•	useful across contexts
	•	not contradicted by stronger evidence
	•	expressed clearly enough for reuse

Keep provisional if:
	•	promising but under-tested
	•	insightful but underspecified
	•	useful metaphor awaiting mechanism

Archive if:
	•	duplicate
	•	outdated
	•	drifted beyond usefulness
	•	context-bound with little transfer value

Reject if:
	•	incoherent
	•	self-sealing
	•	purely aesthetic with no operator value
	•	actively destabilizing to continuity

